notes: Notes from Flann et al. 2010 Taxon 59: Type - Artemisia campestris L. (O. campestris (L.) Cass. in Cuvier , Dict. Sci. Nat. 36: 25 1825) Notes: The name first appears, as a nomen nudum, in Cuvier, Dict. Sci. Nat. 2 (Suppl.): 75 1816. The phrase ‘genre ou sous-genre’ is used in the protologue, with no definite statement as to what genus the subgenus would belong to. ING treats the name as typified by Pfeiffer (1871--1875), on the grounds that Cassini in the protologue includes several Artemisia species in his genus; however, only one of them, A. campestris, is mentioned by name. The combination ‘O. campestris’ was not published in the generic protologue.
